'''訊息流行病'''（{{lang-en|Infodemic}}，或称为'''信息疫情'''）是指关于某种事物（如疾病）的准确資訊與不准确資訊一同被現代網路迅速和广泛地传播。由於事实和谣言的魚龍混雜，人们很难真正了解有關某種事物的正確的基本信息，可能导致人们在認識該疾病或需要尋求帮助时，找不到正确指引反可能被虚假信息所误导，從而發生防疫破口或社會動亂，並造成疫情惡化<ref name=gua2018>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guancha.cn/politics/2020_02_19_537243.shtml|title=27名科学家柳叶刀发声明：强烈谴责新冠非自然起源的阴谋论|website=www.guancha.cn}}</ref>。

== 历史 ==
2003年[[SARS疫情|SARS疫情]]期間，訊息流行病的英文Infodemic一詞就已出現<ref>{{Cite news|author=Rothkopf|first=D. J.|date=14 May 2003|title=SARS also spurs an 'information epidemic':|work=Newsday|url=https://search.proquest.com/newspapers/sars-also-spurs-information-epidemic/docview/279705520/se-2?accountid=203173|accessdate=2020-12-12}}</ref>，在[[2019冠状病毒病疫情|2019冠状病毒病疫情]]时該詞又被重新提及<ref>{{Cite web|title=Words We're Watching: 'Infodemic'|url=https://www.merriam-webster.com/words-at-play/words-were-watching-infodemic-meaning|work=www.merriam-webster.com|access-date=2021-01-22|archive-date=2021-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319170106/https://www.merriam-webster.com/words-at-play/words-were-watching-infodemic-meaning|dead-url=no}}</ref>，例如2020年3月31日，[[联合国|联合国]]和[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]就又开始提到訊息流行病一词<ref>{{Cite web|title=UN tackles 'infodemic' of misinformation|url=https://www.un.org/en/un-coronavirus-communications-team/un-tackling-%E2%80%98infodemic%E2%80%99-misinformation-and-cybercrime-covid-19|access-date=2021-01-22|archive-date=2021-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319170032/https://www.un.org/en/un-coronavirus-communications-team/un-tackling-%E2%80%98infodemic%E2%80%99-misinformation-and-cybercrime-covid-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2020年10月，[[英國國家學術院|英国]][[皇家学会|皇家学会]]和[[英國國家學術院|英国科学院]]在发表的一份联合报告中谈到訊息流行病时表示：「[[2019冠状病毒病疫苗|2019冠状病毒病疫苗]]的開展面临着一个[[信息不对称|信息不对称]]的问题，人們往往接受了错误的信息，其特点是：(1)对科学的不信任；(2)对制药公司和政府的不信任；(3)過度簡化的解釋；(4)意氣用事；(5)[[回声室效应|回声室效应]]<ref name="rsba">{{Cite book|title=COVID-19 vaccine deployment: Behaviour, ethics, misinformation and policy strategies|date=21 October 2020|publisher=Royal Society|url=https://royalsociety.org/-/media/policy/projects/set-c/set-c-vaccine-deployment.pdf?la=en-GB&hash=43073E5429C87FD2674201CA19280A8E|access-date=2021-01-22|archive-date=2021-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319170025/https://royalsociety.org/-/media/policy/projects/set-c/set-c-vaccine-deployment.pdf?la=en-GB&hash=43073E5429C87FD2674201CA19280A8E|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="sksav">{{Cite news|author=Knapton|first=Sarah|title=Spreading anti-vaxx myths 'should be made a criminal offence'|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/11/10/spreading-anti-vaxx-myths-should-made-criminal-offence/|publisher=Telegraph Media Group Limited|date=10 November 2020|accessdate=2021-01-22|archive-date=2021-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319170040/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/11/10/spreading-anti-vaxx-myths-should-made-criminal-offence/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

